H
owever, closing the gates for a little bit to give me/whoever a chance to run around it and ensure it is up to scratch is perhaps a good idea.  Need to balance the need for areas for people to explore and having a fully working city.  Working by the 80% w
orking, 20% not, I would say players should be able to reach it now.  By carriage of course, which can be implemented via a substantial bribe_prog.  Same for Ru\rquote Katta.  This will have to do until we have the roads in place.  
\par 
\par As for what they are doing, as I suggested above, they could be in negotiations with the Fists because of the amount of banditry hampering their trade at present, whether they think it is the fault of the Fists or not.]
